http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/Follow-traffic-rules-students-told/article14026489.ece

An awareness programme on road safety was organised by the Transport Department at Sri Prakash Vidyaniketan here on Thursday.Deputy Transport Commissioner S. Venkateswara Rao, who participated as chief guest, impressed upon the students on the need to abide by traffic rules at all times for the safety of all road users. He said that a majority of the road accident victims were two-wheeler riders and this indicates the importance of wearing helmets.The other major causes of accidents include: driving under the influence of alcohol, cell phone driving and over-speeding. Children below 18 years of age should not drive motor vehicles. A PowerPoint presentation on ‘road safety’ drew the attention of the children.